we are able to connect students with the care that fits their needs best.       Student Assistance Request           Student Resources by Topic  We rely on our partnerships on campus to provide support to students through the Student Assistance area. Our office makes many referrals to both on and off-campus resources. For a list of some of the resources we often refer to, check out the link below.     Click here        Text only Tiles        Care Facts          U and I Care Fund  Give or apply to this emergency fund that's used to support students with one-time urgent needs          U & I Care Plan  UIC’s network of care for students          Large Tiles           Meet Our Partners  Get to know the campus and external partners providing resources for a variety of student concerns             News & Events  Stay up-to-date with U and I Care events and news and that may affect our UIC community               Peer Care Team  Peer Care Team members serve as student advocates of the U and I Care program who provide support and assistance to students. Peer Care team members are dedicated to the holistic success of their peers and help to promote a positive college experience to UIC students. They provide direct support to students, connect them to on-campus resources, conduct educational outreach activities, and assist the functions of the Student Assistance area in the Office of the Dean of Students.   Learn More         You Are Welcome to UIC          How can I contribute?  A gift can be made online          Assistance    Back to main content           Academic Concerns     Academic Resources    Academic Grievances    Withdrawal    Emergencies and Absences      Health & Personal Concerns     Hospitalization & Emergencies    Mental Health    Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns    Housing Instability & Food Insecurity    Financial Concerns    Cannabis: Know the Facts      Campus Life    Faculty & Staff Resources     The Student Response Team    Behavioral Response Interv